OL,5, A top Tibetan leader has defended the  
OL,6, Dalai Lama over a video that showed him
OL,7, asking a child to suck his tongue.     
OL,9,FPenpa Tsering, head of Tibet's         
OL,10,Fgovernment-in-exile, has called the    
OL,11,Fspiritual leader's actions "innocent"  
OL,12,Fand said it demonstrated his           
OL,13,F"affectionate behaviour".              
OL,15,FThe video sparked outrage after it went
OL,16,Fviral on social media, with users      
OL,17,Fcalling his actions inappropriate.     
OL,19,FThe Dalai Lama's office has apologised 
OL,20,Fover the incident.                     
